    <h2>About The Game</h2>
    <div class="span-11">
      <p>
        Rise O' The Urchins was developed by <%= link_to "Dark Tide Software", darktide_path %>
        and won two out of six awards at the UIC video game design class competition. The first award
        was for best graphics and animation and the second award was for best music and sound effects.
        Check out the
        <%= link_to "awards and other games", 'http://www1.cs.uic.edu/www/news.php?audience=public&label=&ind=382' %>
        that participated in the comptetion.
      </p>
      <p>
        Rise O' The Urchins is a multiplayer game created for UIC's or LSU's tactile. The tactile is 
        a multi touch 52-inch LCD tabletop display. The game's objective is to sink pirate ships
        with sea urchins. There are two teams battling to sink as many ships before the time runs out.
        Everytime a ship sinks, the appropriate team receives a sum of gold based on the size of the
        sunken ship.
      </p>
      <p>
        To interact with the game, a player must place a finger on top of an urchin and proceed to drag their
        finger up the screen and lift their finger off the table. This will fling the urchin through the water
        in the direction of the finger motion. Many urchins can be flung in one motion by placing many fingers
        on top of urchins and proceeding to drag fingers up the screen and release. Check out the gameplay video
        to see a 
        <%= link_to "physical demonstration.", 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ys4L3LpYapc', :id => "video_1",
            :rel => "prettyPhoto[videos]"%>
        of Rise O' The Urchins.
      </p>
    </div>
      <div class="span-11 last">
      <p>
        The game contains obstacles and upgrades. The obstacles are sharks, turtles, and explosive pirate kegs.
        Sharks will hunt urchins down if they are struck by an urchin. Turtles are slow lumbering obstacles 
        that just provide a barrier to the top of the screen. Explosive pirate kegs are exactly what they sound,
        they will kill urchins that are too close when they explode.
      </p>
      <p>
        There are four upgrades in the game. They include the heavy, bomber, puffer, and ninja urchin. The heavy urchin
        is twice the weight of any other urchin which allows him to sink boats faster. The bomber urchin is capable
        of blowing a boat up by himself, he may kill other urchins if they are too close. The puffer fish, not an
        urchin at all, will float in the water. She will take an extraordinarily long time to sink to the bottom
        of the ocean. The ninja urchin teleports through the water. This gives him the advantage of being
        able to dodge obstacles and attaching to the top side of a boat.
        Check out the photo gallery to view the different upgrades, obstacles, and screen shots.
      </p>
    </div>
